  "text": "The activity recognition scenario presented in this section is plug-and-play. This means that the target user does not need to label any data and can freely carry the smartphone on any of the seven on-body positions. The results of the plug-and-play mode for the proposed model are shown in Table 6 . The table shows that the correct activity was recognized with an F-measure of 78%. We noticed that the performance of the proposed model in the plug-and-play scenario was similar to the best position-dependent (waist) in [CITATION_1] (see next section). It is worth mentioning that the model in [CITATION_2] does not evaluate the performance of the plug-and-play scenario. Table 6 . Precision, Recall, and F-measure of the proposed model for position-independent and subject-independent HAR. In this scenario, we evaluated the proposed method against different on-body positions. It was important to evaluate the position-dependent HAR since it could be used as a final step for the position-aware HAR. Table 7 shows the F-measure of the proposed model across all seven positions.",
